PLACEHOLDER — not a real executable.

Tauri's `externalBin` existence check requires a file at this exact path/name before
a Windows build will start. Replace it with the real frozen API by running, on Windows:

    powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts\build_sidecar_win.ps1

The sidecar launch in src/lib.rs is best-effort: if this placeholder is still in place
the app still runs (the license gate is pure Rust/JS), the dashboards just show
"API not reachable" until the real binary is present.
